abstract: Democratic presidential contender Joe Biden on Friday criticized President Donald Trump for reducing U.S. oversight of global health issues before the coronavirus outbreak.
snippet: Democratic presidential contender Joe Biden on Friday criticized President Donald Trump for reducing U.S. oversight of global health issues before the coronavirus outbreak.
lead_paragraph: FORT MADISON, Iowa — Democratic presidential contender Joe Biden on Friday criticized President Donald Trump for reducing U.S. oversight of global health issues before the coronavirus outbreak.
headline_main: Biden Slams Trump for Cutting Health Programs Before Coronavirus Outbreak
headline_print_headline: Biden Slams Trump for Cutting Health Programs Before Coronavirus Outbreak

abstract: Two women were arrested in Florida after police opened fire on them for running two security checkpoints near Mar-a-Lago on Friday in a car chase that was unrelated to U.S. President Donald Trump's resort, officials said.
snippet: Two women were arrested in Florida after police opened fire on them for running two security checkpoints near Mar-a-Lago on Friday in a car chase that was unrelated to U.S. President Donald Trump's resort, officials said.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Two women were arrested in Florida after police opened fire on them for running two security checkpoints near Mar-a-Lago on Friday in a car chase that was unrelated to U.S. President Donald Trump's resort, officials said.
headline_main: Two Women in Custody for Running Checkpoints at Trump's Florida Resort
headline_print_headline: Two Women in Custody for Running Checkpoints at Trump's Florida Resort

abstract: He closed with a rhyme of sorts about Joe Biden’s ability to defeat President Trump.
snippet: He closed with a rhyme of sorts about Joe Biden’s ability to defeat President Trump.
lead_paragraph: NORTH LIBERTY — John Kerry, the former secretary of state and presidential nominee, had just ticked through Joseph R. Biden Jr.’s record and his character as he urged Iowans to caucus for his longtime Senate colleague. Then he closed with a rhyme of sorts about Mr. Biden’s ability to defeat President Trump.

abstract: The Democratic Party on Friday announced new rules around how  presidential hopefuls can qualify to take part in debates,  changes likely to allow billionaire media mogul Michael Bloomberg to join the stage in February.
snippet: The Democratic Party on Friday announced new rules around how  presidential hopefuls can qualify to take part in debates,  changes likely to allow billionaire media mogul Michael Bloomberg to join the stage in February.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The Democratic Party on Friday announced new rules around how presidential hopefuls can qualify to take part in debates, changes likely to allow billionaire media mogul Michael Bloomberg to join the stage in February.
headline_main: Democrats Announce New Debate Rules Likely to Allow Bloomberg to Join
headline_print_headline: Democrats Announce New Debate Rules Likely to Allow Bloomberg to Join

abstract: Stuck in Washington as a juror in President Donald Trump's impeachment trial while rivals for the Democratic Party's presidential nomination crisscross Iowa, Senator Elizabeth Warren has tapped a stand-in with undeniable voter appeal: her dog Bailey.
snippet: Stuck in Washington as a juror in President Donald Trump's impeachment trial while rivals for the Democratic Party's presidential nomination crisscross Iowa, Senator Elizabeth Warren has tapped a stand-in with undeniable voter appeal: her dog Bail...
lead_paragraph: COUNCIL BLUFFS, Iowa — Stuck in Washington as a juror in President Donald Trump's impeachment trial while rivals for the Democratic Party's presidential nomination crisscross Iowa, Senator Elizabeth Warren has tapped a stand-in with undeniable voter appeal: her dog Bailey.
headline_main: Democrat Warren Sends Star Stand-In to Iowa: Her Dog Bailey
headline_print_headline: Democrat Warren Sends Star Stand-In to Iowa: Her Dog Bailey

abstract: Republican U.S. Senator Mitt Romney on Friday will vote in favour of allowing witnesses to testify in the Senate's impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, his spokeswoman said.
snippet: Republican U.S. Senator Mitt Romney on Friday will vote in favour of allowing witnesses to testify in the Senate's impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, his spokeswoman said.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Republican U.S. Senator Mitt Romney on Friday will vote in favour of allowing witnesses to testify in the Senate's impeachment trial of President Donald Trump, his spokeswoman said.
headline_main: U.S. Senator Romney to Vote for Trump Impeachment Trial Witnesses
headline_print_headline: U.S. Senator Romney to Vote for Trump Impeachment Trial Witnesses

abstract: U.S. Ambassador to the United Nations Kelly Craft warned the Palestinians on Friday that bringing their displeasure with the U.S. peace plan to the world body would only "repeat the failed pattern of the last seven decades."
snippet: U.S. Ambassador to the United Nations Kelly Craft warned the Palestinians on Friday that bringing their displeasure with the U.S. peace plan to the world body would only "repeat the failed pattern of the last seven decades."
lead_paragraph: UNITED NATIONS — U.S. Ambassador to the United Nations Kelly Craft warned the Palestinians on Friday that bringing their displeasure with the U.S. peace plan to the world body would only "repeat the failed pattern of the last seven decades."
headline_main: U.S. Envoy Warns Palestinians Against Raising Opposition to U.S. Peace Plan at U.N.
headline_print_headline: U.S. Envoy Warns Palestinians Against Raising Opposition to U.S. Peace Plan at U.N.

abstract: Democratic presidential candidates promised voters in Iowa on Saturday they would unify the party to take on President Donald Trump even as they kept up their criticism of each other and navigated the lingering divides from the 2016 campaign.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidates promised voters in Iowa on Saturday they would unify the party to take on President Donald Trump even as they kept up their criticism of each other and navigated the lingering divides from the 2016 campaign.
lead_paragraph: NORTH LIBERTY, Iowa — Democratic presidential candidates promised voters in Iowa on Saturday they would unify the party to take on President Donald Trump even as they kept up their criticism of each other and navigated the lingering divides from the 2016 campaign.
headline_main: Democrats Focus on Unity as Tensions From 2016 Linger
headline_print_headline: Democrats Focus on Unity as Tensions From 2016 Linger

abstract: February kicks off the presidential nominating contest for both the Democratic and Republican parties.
snippet: February kicks off the presidential nominating contest for both the Democratic and Republican parties.
lead_paragraph: (Reuters) - February kicks off the presidential nominating contest for both the Democratic and Republican parties.

abstract: President Trump’s executive order granting local officials veto power over refugee resettlement has divided communities and left immigrants feeling unwanted.
